    // If a_1 and a_n are in the same subsequence, then a_1 + a_2 and a_{n-1} + a_n are candidates for min_f and max_f respectively.
    // But we are considering a partition where a_1 and a_n are in different subsequences.
    // So, min_f = a_1 + a_2 (if a_1, a_2 are in same) or a_1 + a_2 + h (if a_1, a_2 are in different).
    // To minimize max_f - min_f, we want min_f to be as large as possible and max_f to be as small as possible.
    // The smallest possible value for f is a_1 + a_2.
    // The largest possible value for f is a_{n-1} + a_n + h.
    //
    // Consider the partition where a_1 is in S1, and a_2, ..., a_n are in S2.
    // min_f:
    //   - a_1 + a_2 + h (a_1 in S1, a_2 in S2)
    //   - a_2 + a_3 (a_2, a_3 in S2)
