            // if we are at index i and perform the step_sub operation.
            // The value a[i] is added to y, and x becomes i - a[i].
            // If i - a[i] is within bounds (1 to n), then the next operation is step_add
            // using a[i - a[i]].
            // The problem structure is that we always start with step_add, then step_sub, then step_add, etc.
            // So, if we are at index `i` and perform `step_sub`, the new `x` is `i - a[i]`.
            // The next operation will be `step_add` using `a[i - a[i]]`.
