            // We need to compute dp_val[k] and dp_next_x[k] for k from 1 to n.
            // Since a[k] can be large, k + a[k] or k - a[k] can jump far.
            // The values a[i] are fixed for i=2..n.
            // For each query, a[1] changes.
            // So, we need to compute dp_val[1] and dp_next_x[1] for each query.
            // The values dp_val[k] and dp_next_x[k] for k=2..n can be precomputed.

